Find the zero roots of the function f(x) = cos(x)-x over the interval  [0.5,1]


Inverse Linear Interpolation Method

x0=.5,x1=1;

x0 =

    0.5000

x2 = x1 - [(cos(x1)-x1)*(x1-x0)] / ((cos(x1)-x1) - (cos(x0)-x0))

x2 =

    0.7255

evaluateLeftBound = cos(x0)-x0

evaluateLeftBound =

    0.3776

evaluateMidpoint = cos(x2)-x2

evaluateMidpoint =

    0.0227

evaluateRightBound = cos(x1)-x1

evaluateRightBound =

   -0.4597

x0 = x2

x0 =

    0.7255

x3 = x1 - [(cos(x1)-x1)*(x1-x0)] / ((cos(x1)-x1) - (cos(x0)-x0))

x3 =

    0.7384

evaluateLeftBound = cos(x0)-x0

evaluateLeftBound =

    0.0227

evaluateMidpoint = cos(x3)-x3

evaluateMidpoint =

    0.0011

evaluateRightBound = cos(x1)-x1

evaluateRightBound =

   -0.4597

x0=x3

x0 =

    0.7384

x4 = x1 - [(cos(x1)-x1)*(x1-x0)] / ((cos(x1)-x1) - (cos(x0)-x0))

x4 =

    0.7391

evaluateLeftBound = cos(x0)-x0

evaluateLeftBound =

    0.0011

evaluateMidpoint = cos(x4)-x4

evaluateMidpoint =

   5.7575e-05

evaluateRightBound = cos(x1)-x1

evaluateRightBound =

   -0.4597

x0=x4

x0 =

    0.7391

x5 = x1 - [(cos(x1)-x1)*(x1-x0)] / ((cos(x1)-x1) - (cos(x0)-x0))

x5 =

    0.7391

evaluateLeftBound = cos(x0)-x0

evaluateLeftBound =

   5.7575e-05

evaluateMidpoint = cos(x5)-x5

evaluateMidpoint =

   2.8842e-06

evaluateRightBound = cos(x1)-x1

evaluateRightBound =

   -0.4597





Bisection Method

>> x=0.5:.125:1;
>> x0=.5,x1=1;

x0 =

    0.5000

>> disp('first iteration')
first iteration
>> midpoint = (x0+x1)/2

midpoint =

    0.7500

>> cos(x0)-x0

ans =

    0.3776

>> cos(midpoint)-midpoint

ans =

   -0.0183

>> cos(x1)-x1

ans =

   -0.4597

>> disp('second iteration')
second iteration
>> x1=midpoint

x1 =

    0.7500

>> midpoint = (x0+x1)/2

midpoint =

    0.6250

>> cos(midpoint)-midpoint

ans =

    0.1860

>> cos(x1)-x1

ans =

   -0.0183

>> disp('third iteration')
third iteration
>> x0=midpoint

x0 =

    0.6250

>> midpoint = (x0+x1)/2

midpoint =

    0.6875

>> cos(x0)-x0

ans =

    0.1860

>> cos(midpoint)-midpoint

ans =

    0.0853

>> disp('fourth iteration')
fourth iteration
>> x0=midpoint

x0 =

    0.6875

>> midpoint = (x0+x1)/2

midpoint =

    0.7188

>> cos(x0)-x0

ans =

    0.0853

>> cos(midpoint)-midpoint

ans =

    0.0339

>> disp('fifth iteration')
fifth iteration
>> x0=midpoint

x0 =

    0.7188

>> midpoint = (x0+x1)/2

midpoint =

    0.7344

>> cos(x0)-x0

ans =

    0.0339

>> cos(midpoint)-midpoint

ans =

    0.0079

